> And when using the GP2D12, it's necesary to cut the resistor pullup out of the
> circuit for the port that the sensor is plugged into, correct? Thus making the
> port useless for the typical light and reflectance sensors that would
> otherwise be easily used in that port?

Why does it make the ports useless for other sensors? If you need a
pullup-resistor,
you can still solder a 47k resistor directly to your sensor-connector
between Vcc and
Sensor in. Thus in my opinion the HB can be used more flexible without
the pullup-resistors.

Further information about connecting the GP2D12 can be found at:
http://condor.informatik.uni-oldenburg.de/stueker/GP2D12

Dirk

